## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Screens and components
  - ClientPortalLayout: Mobile-first shell with responsive sidebar and topbar
  - BrandingHeader: Logo, project name, and inline instructions
  - DecisionCardPanel: Side-by-side options with large CTAs, thumbnail previews
  - DecisionCardItem: Renders a single decision with title, status, and latest activity
  - CommentThread: Nested comments with threading, mentions, and attachments
  - MentionAutocomplete: Lightweight user picker for mentions within comments
  - ApprovalBar: Primary Approve button, optional typed name box, timestamp display
  - ActivityTimeline: Audit trail for decisions
  - AttachmentsView: List and preview of attachments
  - NotificationInbox: In-app notification list
  - SuccessPage: Generic success confirmation layout
  - DecisionDetailPage: Comprehensive view including comparison, comments, history, and actions
  - ShareExportPanel: UI for sharing/exporting decisions
  - FollowUpTaskCreator: Quick task creation tied to a decision
- UI states
  - Loading, error, empty states
  - Disabled/disabled-within-state for action buttons when appropriate
- Accessibility
  - WCAG 2.1 AA compliance where feasible
  - Keyboard navigable, proper aria-labels, and readable color contrast
- Responsive behaviors
  - Sidebar collapsible on mobile; topbar stays fixed
  - Cards stack vertically on narrow viewports; horizontal scrolling for long option lists if needed
- Data handling
  - Local state for optimistic UI updates; fallback to server on error
- Animations
  - Subtle transitions for navigation expand/collapse, hover lifts, and focus rings

### Backend
- Data models (simplified for scope)
  - Decision
    - id, projectId, title, createdBy, createdAt, updatedAt, status, auditTrail
  - DecisionOption
    - id, decisionId, name, description, mediaUrl, priceEstimate, swatch
  - Comment
    - id, decisionId, parentCommentId, authorId, content, createdAt, attachments[]
  - Attachment
    - id, commentId or decisionAssetId, filename, url, mimeType, size
  - Approval
    - id, decisionId, approverName, approvedAt, status (approved/declined/pending), note
  - AuditLog
    - id, decisionId, action, actor, timestamp, details
  - Notification
    - id, recipient, type, message, link, read, createdAt
  - Branding
    - studioId, logoUrl, colorPalette, customDomain (optional), domainStatus
- APIs (internal)
  - GET /portal/decisions?token={token} -> list of decisions accessible via token
  - GET /portal/decision/{id} -> detailed decision with options, comments, attachments
  - POST /portal/decision/{id}/comment -> create comment (with attachments, mentions)
  - POST /portal/decision/{id}/approve -> submit approval (with optional confirm name)
  - POST /portal/decision/{id}/export -> generate/export decision log
  - POST /portal/decision/{id}/followup -> create follow-up task
  - GET /portal/notifications -> fetch in-app notifications
  - POST /portal/branding -> save branding changes for the client link
  - POST /portal/token/refresh -> refresh token before expiry (if applicable)
  - GET /portal/token/status -> token expiry and security notice
- Database considerations
  - Use relational store for decisions, options, comments, approvals, and audit logs
  - Attachments stored in object storage with secure signed URLs
  - Index decisions by token, projectId, and decisionId for fast access
- Validation and error handling
  - Validate required fields for comments, approvals
  - Enforce token-scoped permissions on all endpoints
  - Rate limiting for comment submissions to prevent spam
- Security
  - Token-based access with time-limited tokens
  - No user accounts required; actions audited with studio user IDs or system actors
  - CSRF protection for state-changing actions via token binding
  - Domain and session security: if custom domain is used, ensure TLS and proper CNAME routing
- Export formats
  - PDF/CSV export of decision logs with timestamps and audit trail

### Integration
- State management
  - Centralized store for decisions, comments, approvals, and notifications
  - Sync between frontend components and backend endpoints with optimistic updates
- Email & In-App notifications
  - Trigger emails on approval, new comments mentions, and export readiness
  - In-app notification feed synchronized with server-side events
- Branding integration
  - Branding data is applied to all client portal views; allow studios to modify branding via API (branding endpoint)
- Asset usage
  - Icon Set & Illustrations loaded from asset kit; fallbacks for missing assets
- Security integration
  - Token validation middleware on all portal endpoints
  - Expiry warnings and token refresh prompts in UI

## User Experience Flow
- Entry
  - Client receives a secure, tokenized link via email or other channel
  - Portal loads decisions accessible by the token; token status checked
  - Branding header renders studio logo and project name
  - Security notice about token expiry is shown upfront
- Decision Review
  - Client sees a decision list (cards) with side-by-side option comparisons
  - Tap a decision to open the Decision Detail Page
  - Review options, view attachments, context notes
- Interaction
  - Comment on decisions with threaded replies
  - Mention colleagues or the studio team to trigger notifications
  - Approve decisions with optional typed name; timestamp appears post-approval
  - Export decision logs or share links
  - Create follow-up tasks linked to decisions
- Feedback & Confirmation
  - After approvals or exports, show the Success / Confirmation Page
  - Email and in-app notifications confirm actions and provide next steps
- Exit
  - Token expiry or user-initiated exit securely ends session; provide a contact support link

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: (Schema overview)
- Decision
  - id, tokenId, projectId, title, summary, createdAt, updatedAt, status, auditTrail
- DecisionOption
  - id, decisionId, name, description, mediaUrl, priceEstimate, swatch
- Comment
  - id, decisionId, parentCommentId, authorId, content, createdAt, attachments[]
- Attachment
  - id, parentType ('decision'|'comment'), parentId, filename, url, mimeType, size
- Approval
  - id, decisionId, approverName, approvedAt, status, note
- AuditLog
  - id, decisionId, action, actorId, timestamp, details
- Branding
  - id, studioId, logoUrl, primaryColor, secondaryColor, backgroundColor, customDomain, domainStatus
- Notification
  - id, recipientId, type, message, link, read, createdAt

API Endpoints (Routes and Methods)
- Portal Access
  - GET /portal/decisions?token={token}
  - GET /portal/decision/{decisionId}
- Decision Actions
  - POST /portal/decision/{decisionId}/comment
  - POST /portal/decision/{decisionId}/approve
  - POST /portal/decision/{decisionId}/export
  - POST /portal/decision/{decisionId}/followup
- Notifications
  - GET /portal/notifications
- Branding & Tokens
  - POST /portal/branding
  - GET /portal/token/status
  - POST /portal/token/refresh

Security
- Token-based authentication for session; token is time-bound and scoped to specific projects/decisions
- No account-based authentication; all actions are tied to token identity and studio audit
- Input validation and sanitization for all user-provided content (comments, attachments, approvals)
- Role-based considerations within token scope (client vs. studio; read/write rights)
- Data encryption at rest and in transit; signed URLs for attachment access

Validation
- Client-side form validation for comment content, attachments, and approval notes
- Server-side validation for token validity, decision existence, and permission checks
- Concurrency handling for approvals (avoid duplicate approvals from same token)
- File validations for attachments (size, type, virus scanning hook)

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Tokenized client portal loads decisions securely and renders branding per studio
- [ ] Clients can view decisions, compare options side-by-side, and attach comments
- [ ] Mentions trigger both in-app and email notifications; assignees receive notifications
- [ ] Approvals produce a timestamp and update the audit trail; subsequent exports reflect the approval
- [ ] Success/Confirmation pages render after approvals and exports
- [ ] Decision Detail Page shows complete info: visual comparison, comments, history, attachments, and actions
- [ ] Custom branding (logo, colors) and optional custom domain render correctly in the client portal
- [ ] Token expiry notice and secure session termination work as expected

UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Use mobile-first, responsive components
- Maintain 12-column layout with generous whitespace and clear typographic hierarchy
- Ensure high contrast text and accessible controls
- Use the provided color palette for consistency and emphasis on action states
- Card, navigation, and data visualization design as described in Visual Style

Visual Style

Color Palette:
- Primary background: #F7F7F9
- Secondary background: #FFFFFF
- Accent: #0052CC
- Grays: #E5E7EB, #D1D5DB, #6B7280, #111827
- Status: #10B981, #F59E42, #EF4444

Typography & Layout:
- Font: Modern geometric sans-serif (Inter, SF Pro, etc.)
- Headings: H1 ~28px, H2 ~22px, H3 ~18px; weight 600–700
- Body: 15–16px, 1.5x line-height
- 12-column grid; 24–32px gutters; left-aligned text

Key Design Elements

Card Design:
- White cards, subtle shadow, 8–12px radius
- Light borders (#E5E7EB)
- Hover: lift or tint (#F3F4F6)
- Title at top; muted metadata; right-aligned status/badge

Navigation:
- Sidebar: Left, #F5F6FA; active item highlight
- Icons: Monochrome line icons, active state filled
- Top bar: White with subtle bottom border
- Collapsible folders with smooth transitions
- Active item: bold text; accent indicator

Data Visualization:
- Minimal charts if present; use accent color; muted gridlines
- Status indicators as pills/dots with status colors

Interactive Elements:
- Buttons: Primary #0052CC, white text; secondary ghost/outline
- Hover/shadow/active/disabled states
- Form fields: Rounded, light borders, focus ring
- Search bars: Full-width, rounded with left icon
- Micro-interactions: Smooth transitions on hover/focus

Design Philosophy
- Modern, minimalist, professional; emphasize clarity and quick decision-making
- High readability, whitespace, consistent color/iconography
- Focus on content, reduce cognitive load, enable fast decisions

Connected Pages:
- Success / Confirmation Page
- Decision Detail Page

Connected Features:
- Responsive Navigation
- Notifications (Email & In-App)
- Decision Objects & Approval Workflow
- Branding & Custom Client Links
- Comments, Mentions & Collaboration
- Client Portal (No-login) Experience

Notes for AI Development Tool
- Produce a cohesive data model and API surface that can be wired to a frontend SPA (React/Next.js or similar) and a Node/Go/Python backend.
- Ensure token-based access is enforced server-side for all endpoints.
- Provide clear data contracts (DTOs) for each API, including input/output shapes.
- Include sample payloads and edge-case scenarios (token expiry, missing attachments, multi-user mentions).
- Include a basic test plan: unit, integration, and end-to-end checks for key flows (load decisions, post-comment with mention, approve decision, export).

